+|io|ruro}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|campo|f}}, {{tt+|it|campagna|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|田舎|tr=いなか, inaka}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|시골}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt|ckb|لادێ}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|gundewar}}\n* Latgalian: {{tt|ltg|sola}}, {{tt|ltg|solys|p}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|rūs|n}}, {{tt+|la|pāgus|m}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|lauki|p}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|kaimas|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt+|mk|село|n}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|pedalaman}}, {{tt+|ms|desa}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|നാട്ടുമ്പുറം}}, {{tt+|ml|ഗ്രാമം}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|contre}}, {{t|enm|lond}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|хөдөө}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|land|n}}, {{tt|nb|landsbygd|m|f}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|land|n}}, {{tt|nn|landsbygd|f}}\n* Old English: {{tt+|ang|land|n}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|روسْتا}}, {{tt|fa-ira|[[حُوْمِهٔ]] [[شَهْر]]}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|wieś|f}}, {{tt+|pl|prowincja|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|campo|m}}, {{tt+|pt|interior}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|țară}}, {{tt+|ro|sat|n}}\n* Romansh: {{tt|rm|cuntrada|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|дере́вня|f}}, {{tt+|ru|село́|n}}, {{tt+|ru|прови́нция|f}}\n* Sardinian: {{tt|sc|sartu|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|dùthaich|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|сѐло|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|sèlo|n}}\n* Sidamo: {{tt|sid|gobba}}\n* Silesian: {{tt|szl|wjeś|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|dedina|f}}, {{tt|sk|vidiek|m}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|podeželje|n}}, {{tt+|sl|dežela|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|campo|m}}, {{tt+|es|campaña|f}}, {{tt+|es|campiña|f}}, {{tt+|es|provincia|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|shamba|c5|c6}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|landsbygd}}, {{tt+|sv|landet}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}, {{tt+|sv|landsort}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|நாடு}}, {{tt+|ta|நாட்டுப்புறம்}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|ชนบท}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|taşra}}, {{tt+|tr|kırsal}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|طیشاری|tr=dışarı}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|село́|n}}, {{tt+|uk|прові́нція|f}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|دیہات|m}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|qishloq}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt|vi|miền quê}}, {{tt+|vi|nông thôn}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|campagne|f}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|cefn gwlad}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|тыа}}, {{tt|sah|тыа сирэ}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ìgbèríko}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|rıstan|c}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|country music}}<!-- Only short forms here, full translations to \"country music\" -->\n* Arabic:\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|كونتري|m|tr=kawntri}}, {{tt|arz|كنتري|m|tr=kantri}}\n* Armenian: {{tt|hy|քանթրի}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|къ́нтри|n}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt|cmn|[[鄉村]][[音樂]]}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|country|m}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|kantri}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kantri}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|country|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|ქანთრი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Country}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|kántrí|n}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|ceol tuaithe|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|カントリー|tr=kantorī}}\n* Korean: {{tt|ko|컨트리}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|kantrī|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt|lt|kantri}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|ка́нтри}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|country}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|country}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|country|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|country|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|ка́нтри|f|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|ranchera|f}}, {{t+|es|country|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|country|c}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|நாட்டு}}\n* Walloon: {{tt|wa|countri|m}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|kontri}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* [[Appendix:Countries of the world]]\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj|er|more}}\n\n# From or in the [[countryside]], connected with it{{,}} or typical of it.\n#: {{ux|en|Things around here are just a little more '''country''' than what he's used to.}}\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=5|passage=When this conversation was repeated in detail within the hearing of the young woman in question, and undoubtedly for his benefit, Mr. Trevor threw shame to the winds and scandalized the Misses Brewster then and there by proclaiming his father to have been a '''country''' storekeeper.}}\n# {{senseid|en|of country music}} Of or connected to [[country music]].\n#: {{ux|en|They're mainly a hard rock band, but their new album sounds kinda '''country''' to me.}}\n# {{lb|en|India}} Originating in [[India]] rather than being imported from [[abroad]].\n#: {{syn|en|native}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1872|title=Silk in India|page=16\n|passage=We have seen that the Company manufactured silk stuffs at three of its Residencies, but from '''country'''-wound silk.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1884|title=Journal of the United Service Institution of India|page=185\n|passage=A reference to the Annual Administration Reports of the Department of Horse-breeding Operations {{...}} will allow of the opinion being arrived at, that the breed of '''country''' horses under the present regime is steadily improving.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1937|author=Brigadier-General H. A. Young|title=The East India Company’s Arsenals & Manufactories\n|passage='''Country''' harness costs nearly as much, lasts half the time, and is in every respect inferior. It is understood that the only reason is that the Court desires to improve and encourage Indian manufactures.}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|en\n|countrify\n|countryish,countrylike\n|go country\n}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|of, from or pertaining to the countryside ''(adjective)''}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|رِيفِيّ}}, {{t|ar|نِسْبَة إِلَى الرِّيف|tr=nisba ʔilā r-rīf}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|գյուղական}}, {{t+|hy|շինական}}\n* Breton: {{t|br|[[diwar]] [[ar]] [[maez]]}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|провинциален}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|campestre}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|鄉下|alt=鄉下的|tr=xiāngxià de}}, {{t+|cmn|鄉村|alt=鄉村的|tr=xiāngcūn de}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|plattelands}}, {{t|nl|boeren-}}, {{t|nl|land-}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|maalainen}}, {{t|fi|maalais-}}, {{t+|fi|maaseutu}}\n* French: {{t|fr|de la [[campagne]]}}, {{t|fr|de [[province]]}}, {{t|fr|de la [[contrée]]}}, {{t+|fr|campagnard}}\n* German: {{t+|de|ländlich}}, {{t|de|Land-}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|αγροτικός}}, {{t+|el|εξοχικός}}, {{t+|el|επαρχιώτικος}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|כפרי|tr=kafry|m}}, {{t|he|כפרית|f|tr=kafryt}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|vidéki}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|desa}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|rural}}, {{t|ia|campestre}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|di [[campagna]]}}, {{t+|it|rurale}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|田舎|tr=いなか, inaka}}, {{t+|ja|田舎|alt=田舎の|tr=いなかの, inaka no}}, {{t+|ja|田園|tr=でんえん, den'en}}, {{t+|ja|地方|alt=地方の|tr=ちほうの, chihō no}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|시골}}, {{t|ko|시골-의}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|rūsticus}}, {{t|la|rūrālis}}, {{t+|la|agrestis}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|lauku}}, {{t|lv|lauku-}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|kaimo}}, {{t|lt|kaimiškas}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|се́лски|m}}\n* Mongolian: {{t|mn|хөдөөний}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|landsens}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|روستایی|tr=rustâyi}}, {{t+|fa|حاشیه نشین}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|wiejski}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|rural}}, {{t+|pt|campestre}}, do [[campo]], {{t+|pt|grosseiro}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|rural}}, {{t+|ro|țara}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|дереве́нский}}, {{t+|ru|се́льский}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|dùthchail}}, {{t|gd|tìreil}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|dedinský}}, {{t|sk|vidiecky}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|podeželski}}, {{t+|sl|vaški}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|campo|alt=de campo}}, {{t+|es|campesino}}, {{t+|es|campestre}}, {{t+|es|provincia|alt=de provincia}}, {{t+|es|provinciano}}, {{t|es|campeño}}, {{t+|es|campero}}, {{t+|es|agreste}}\n* Swahili: {{t|sw|-a kimashamba}}\n* Swedish: {{t|sv|land-}}, {{t|sv|lands-}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|நாட்டு}}, {{t|ta|நாட்டுப்புற}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|ทางชนบท|tr=thaang chohn bòht}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|kırsal}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|דאָרפֿיש}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|rıstan|c}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|of or connected to country music}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|country}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n* {{R:Keywords 21st}}\n* {{R:Keywords|page=81}}\n* {{R:Longman|text=an area of land that is suitable for a particular activity, has particular features, or is connected with a particular person or people}}\n* {{cite-web|en|work=Oxford Languages|nodate=1|entryurl=https://www.google.com/search?q=define+country|entry=country|text=an area or region with regard to its physical features. [...] a region associated with a particular person, especially a writer, or with a particular work.|publisher=w:Oxford University Press}}\n* {{R:OED Online|pos=n}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913|text=The inhabitants or people of a state or a region; the populace; the public.|pos=n}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n{{c|en|Geography}}\n\n==Basque==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{eu-pr|kauntri}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{eu-noun|in}}\n\n# [[country music]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{eu-ndecl|in.sg}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:eu:EH}}\n\n{{C|eu|Music}}\n\n==Danish==\n{{wp|da:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|da|en|country}}. {{etydate|1969}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|-}}\n\n# {{lb|da|music}} {{l|en|country}}, [[country music]]\n#: {{syn|da|countrymusik|country og western}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{da-decl|en|n=sg}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|da|countrysanger}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n{{C|da|Musical genres}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{l|fi|kantri}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|fi|en|country}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-pronunciation|kantri}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# [[country music]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{fi-decl-valo|countr|||y|a|n=sg}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|fi|countrymusiikki}}\n* {{l|fi|kantrimusiikki}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fi|title=compounds\n|countrymusiikki\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2023-07-02}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|fr|en|-}}. {{doublet|fr|contrée}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|keuntri}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-country.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[country music]]\n\n{{C|fr|Musical genres}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|it|en|country}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|càuntry,!càntry<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# {{lb|it|music}} [[country music]]\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:muzyka +}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{pseudo-loan|pl|en|country music}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-country.ogg|kantry|h=coun.try}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|n|indecl=yes}}\n\n# {{l|en|country}}, [[country music]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adjectives|country'owy|countrowy}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Musical genres}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|country}}. The pronunciation reflects the incorrect belief that the {{angbr IPA|oun}} represents {{IPAchar|/aʊn/}} in the English etymon.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|br=cáw̃.tri,cãtri}}<!--bastard phonemes-->\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[country music]]\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{C|pt|Musical genres}}\n\n==Romanian==\n{{wp|ro:}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|ro|кантри||new cyrl}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|ro|en|country}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/ˈkan.tri/}}\n* {{rhyme|ro|antri|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|ro|coun|try}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{ro-adj}}\n\n# {{l|en|country}} {{gl|music}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-decl-adj}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DEX}}\n\n==Spanish==\n{{wp|es:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|country}}. {{doublet|es|contrada}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|kantri,kontri|kowntri,kowntrí|hyph=+}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[country music]]\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sv|en|country}}. {{etydate|1965}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c|-}}\n\n# {{lb|sv|music}} {{l|en|country}}, [[country music]]\n#: {{syn|sv|countrymusik}}\n#* {{quote-song|sv|author=w:Claes Eriksson|year=1986|artist=w:Per Fritzell|album=Macken|trans-album=The gas station|title=Truckdriving song|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fMn7vnpwhcM|text=Howdy, cowboy! Visa nu, vad har du på din mack? Jag behöver fylla skafferiet på min truck [English]. Tuggummi, så klart, snus och chips, en låda dryck, skulle jag bli glad om jag fick. Jag drar min långtradarsång, min lastbilskörarsång, för jag har sån smak för bilar med flak. Jag drar min truckdriving song [English], tjugofyra meter lång, och jag tackar Gud för '''countryns''' alla ljud. Och om låten blir för tråkig, ja, då jag tar jag det kallt. Ja, då byter jag tonart och höjer ett halvt. Ja, jag höjer ett halvt.|t=Howdy, cowboy! Show me now, what do you have at your gas station? I need to fill the pantry in my truck [English]. Chewing gum, of course, {{l|sv|snus}} and chips [in the US sense], a case of drink, I would be happy if I got. I do [pull] my big rig song, my truck driving song, because I have such taste for cars with a flatbed [platform]. I do my truckdriving song [English], twenty-four meters long, and I thank God for all the sounds '''of country music''' (\"for '''the country music's''' all sounds\"). And if the song gets too boring, yes, then I stay cool [take it cool]. Yes, then I change the key and raise by a half [step]. Yes, I raise by a half [step].}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-noun-unc-irreg-c}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:svenska.se}}\n\n{{C|sv|Musical genres}}"}}